cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the use of multiple antennas at a relay to improve the performance of a bidirectional communication system. Information theory is concerned with the fundamental limits of communication systems, and this paper presents results on the benefits of using different relay strategies. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of wireless network coding to improve the performance of the communication system. This is a networking technique that can improve the efficiency of data transmission in wireless networks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers the use of different relay strategies and antenna selection to improve the performance of the communication system. This involves designing and analyzing control systems for the communication system. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of multiple antennas and wireless network coding to improve the transmission of multimedia data in the communication system. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper presents results on the performance of different relay strategies and antenna selection schemes, which involves computational analysis and optimization.
